(18, 18, 'product_cat', '<h3>Modern Area Rug Stores Miami</h3>\r\nAt Grand Oriental Rug Gallery we carry the exquisite designer contemporary area rugs to satisfy your artistic plate. you will discover a range of contemporary area rugs in exotic patterns, Modern designs. contemporary area rugs are made in wool, silk, and combination of both. Come and choose from The Modern Tibetan contemporary area rug for your fashionable seating arrangement.', 0, 5),
(19, 19, 'product_cat', '<h3>Persian, Area, Oushak, Antique, Tabriz, Ispfhan. Naine, Kashan, Silk Qums, Ziegler, Mahal. Modern, Tibetan, Nepalese, carpets, cowhide rugs, Animal print Vegetable dyes, Kashmir silk, Bamboo silk, contemporary, transitional carpets, striped cowhide rugs, Rugs Miami.</h3>\r\n<div class=\"block-heading-text\">When talking about traditional rugs, the terms Oriental Rugs, or Persian rugs come to mind. The art, mystique, and history of Oriental Rugs make the search for them very intoxicating. History has shown that Oriental rugs stand for their captivating/marveling designs, uncompromising quality, durability, and value.\r\n<b>What’s the difference?</b>\r\nOriental rug refers to a hand-woven rug made from wool, silk or cotton, woven in the Orient (a historic term for Asia), specifically Iran, China, India, Russia, Turkey, Pakistan, Tibet and Nepal. Persian rug refers to carpets exclusively woven in the Islamic Republic of Iran (before 1935, Persia).</div>', 0, 0),
(20, 20, 'product_cat', '<h3>The best selection of Tibetan hand knotted silk &amp; wool , pashmina &amp; silk blend rugs, custom sizes available.</h3>\r\n<div class=\"block-heading-text\">Tibetan area rugs a tradition and culture of ages, in the heart of Himalayan Mountains. our hand knotted Tibetan rugs are made of Silk or Silk and Tibetan Pashmina Wool combination. Tibetan rugs are mostly made in Modern and Contemporary designs.</div>', 0, 0),
(21, 21, 'product_cat', '<h3>Animal Prints / Cowhides Rugs</h3>\r\n<div class=\"block-heading-text\">Sustainably sourced from both India and the South American pampas, each one-of-a-kind cowhide rug has a lustrous sheen, contrasting spots, and a broad range of background hues that come alive in natural daylight.</div>', 0, 1),
(22, 22, 'product_cat', '<h3>Aubusson Area Rugs. Aubusson Rugs.</h3>\r\n<div class=\"block-heading-text\">With its name originating from the French village of Aubusson near the Creuse River, these were first woven around the 16 th century and were symbolic of elegance and prestige of Imperial France. Today, the Aubusson still reflects this notion.</div>', 0, 1),
(23, 23, 'product_cat', '<h3>Persian, Area, Oushak, Antique, Tabriz, Ispfhan. Naine, Kashan, Silk Qums, Ziegler, Mahal. Modern, Tibetan, Nepalese, carpets, cowhide rugs, Animal print Vegetable dyes, Kashmir silk, Bamboo silk, contemporary, transitional carpets, striped cowhide rugs, Rugs Miami.</h3>\r\n<div class=\"block-heading-text\">When talking about traditional rugs, the terms Oriental Rugs, or Persian rugs come to mind. The art, mystique, and history of Oriental Rugs make the search for them very intoxicating. History has shown that Oriental rugs stand for their captivating/marveling designs, uncompromising quality, durability, and value.\r\n<b>What’s the difference?</b>\r\nOriental rug refers to a hand-woven rug made from wool, silk or cotton, woven in the Orient (a historic term for Asia), specifically Iran, China, India, Russia, Turkey, Pakistan, Tibet and Nepal. Persian rug refers to carpets exclusively woven in the Islamic Republic of Iran (before 1935, Persia).</div>', 0, 0),
